@NODE HISTORY "History"

                                   @{FG shine}@{b}HISTORY@{FG text}@{ub}
                                   @{FG shine}@{b}-------@{FG text}@{ub}

 @{b}V1.8, Pegase 1.80 (31.8.2000)@{ub} :
  - Final release.

 @{b}V1.8b, Pegase 1.81 (3.9.2000)@{ub} :
  - The original filename extension is no longer replaced by ".mp?" if it
    begins with a decimal digit. Thus, an audio CD track named "track.2"
    will not overwrite "track.mp2" silently, created by a previous  track
    named "track.1", as this was the case before.

 @{b}V1.8d, Pegase 1.83 (9.9.2000)@{ub} :
  - The output quality has been improved.

 @{b}V1.8e, Pegase 1.84 (11.9.2000)@{ub} :
  - Bitstreams produced from 32/48 KHz sampled datas were wrong.

 @{b}V1.8f, Pegase 1.85 (13.9.2000)@{ub} :
  - The psycho-acoustic analyzer has been polished.
  - The modified threshold table used for 32 KHz sampled datas was
    erroneously computed for 38 KHz sampled datas.
  - The 'FREQ' keyword may be used to select the sampling rate when encoding
    CDDA files (or samples sent through a PIPE).

 @{b}V1.8g, Pegase 1.86 (23.9.2000)@{ub} :
  - Layer 1 SNR and Quantization tables have been fixed (long standing bug).
  - The absolute threshold tables have been changed again.
  - Little speedup due to a lower attenuation limit in the spreading
    function.
  - Little modification on the scale factors select information patterns
    (Layer 2) in order to better match the subband levels in some cases.

@ENDNODE

